Last month, I had the priviledge of being invited as the first alumni pass-out of computer science & business systems department, for giving a small guest lecture on placement preparation. Being a guy, with 1.5 years internship experience and 9 months work experience, I wasn't sure if I was even eligible to give an alumni talk. But I took this as an opportunity to share my placement experience with companies and how things worked out for me.

I started the session with a positive note, addressing them and then explained them the importance of resume, internships, rounds of interview, mock GD and interview prep and tips to perform better in technical interview. Also, I provided them, the compilation of all the resources that i used during my placements. 

I would like to thank the Head of the department, Dean and faculty members of Rajalakshmi Institute of Technology for the wonderful opportunity.

I took this session, not because I knew everything. When I was at their age, I had no brother or sister to teach me on what to prepare and how to. So I took this golden opportunity to share few words to make sure that something from that saession can help them come out with their dream jobs!
